<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-1212] System test exception handling does not stop background producer threads</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-1212</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When exception is thrown, the system test script stops all known entities. However, the background producer thread cannot be stopped since it does not register its pid in the testcase environment. We need to specifically stop them.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
